node.text: Books like “How to Be An Anti-Racist” have no place in our military. Not only are these books on OFFICIAL reading lists, but they’re being promoted as suggested readings with fliers and advertisements. And the critical race theory taught in these books is being manifested into actual training, propagandize to our service members with things like privilege walks. It’s depleting morale, ruining the reputation of our military, and needs to stop.

“White Privilege: Unpacking the Invisible Knapsack”
This training manual from 1989 is pulled right from the teachings of critical race theory. And service members at the Special Operations Command are being pushed to read it. The manual argues that everything should be viewed through the lens of privilege and racism, and seeks to debunk any notion of a “meritocracy.” It’s exactly the sort of woke ideology that should be nowhere near our military.

May be an image of text that says 'Dan Crenshaw @DanCrenshawTX Joe Biden has an open doo policy for illegal immigrants who wear his campaign shirts when crossing our southern border. But he shuts the door on America-loving Cubans fleeing a communist regime and Afghans who risked their lives for U.S. troops.'.

node.text: We should be grateful for the freedoms we have. Don’t forget that. And don’t let power-hungry politicians take those freedoms from you, claiming they’re doing it for your own good.

node.text: Everyone has been asking: can someone tell us what’s actually in these Texas election reform bills? The Democrats keep saying they’re bad but they won’t say why. Well, here is what they do. Swipe right.
